This paper discusses the use of Q&A hashtags on Twitter, which falls under the category of social media and social networks. The paper also mentions log analysis and designing next-generation social search systems, which could be related to information retrieval and cybersecurity. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Societal Computing). The paper also touches upon natural language processing (NLP) and community monitoring, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity). Finally, the paper mentions the use of hashtags for topical signifiers, which could be related to information retrieval and search engines, hence cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
